Stan Mathabatha has been elected for a third term as ANC Limpopo chairperson (eNCA/Screenshot) POLOKWANE - Stan Mathabatha has been re-elected as the ANC Limpopo Provincial chairperson. He retains the position for a third term. Mathabatha convincingly beat Dickson Masemola with 789 votes to 389. READ: Stan Mathabatha retains ANC's Limpopo chair position Addressing the media after his victory, Mathabatha says all ANC members must rally behind the elected leaders. Addressing the media after his victory, Stan Mathabatha says all ANC members must rally behind the elected leaders. He retains the chairperson position for a third term. #DSTV403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/FEIbLhmbor Meanwhile, Mathabatha says the quality of service delivery will be top of the agenda. He says the performance of deployees in government will also be in the spotlight. Stan Mathabatha says the quality of service delivery will be top of the agenda. He says the performance of deployees in government will also be in the spotlight. #DStv403 pic.twitter.com/Ffhm50gKXO